.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Francoise, Herve, Marcel, Philippe, Pierre.","French: topographic name for someone who lived on or near a hill, from Old French <i>montaine</i> ‘hill, (small) mountain’; or a habitational name from any of several places called (La) Montagne, named with the same word.","Shortened form of French   Lamontagne  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mountain","meanings":["English (Yorkshire; of Norman origin): topographic name from Middle English <i>mountaine</i> ‘mountain’ (Old French <i>montagne</i>). See   Montagne  .","Irish: either of Norman origin, as 1 above, or a variant of   Manton  .","English: variant of <b>Monkton</b> a habitational name from Monkton (Kent, Somerset), Moor Monkton and Nun Monkton (Yorkshire), Bishop Monkton (Yorkshire), or any of numerous other places called Monkton, named with Old English <i>munuc</i> ‘monk’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]},{"name":"Lamontagne","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Lucien, Marcel, Emile, Pierre, Aime, Andre, Fernand, Normand, Gaston, Ovide, Achille.","French:","habitational name for someone from any of several places called La Montagne, or a variant of the topographic name   Montagne   1, with fused feminine definite article <i>la</i>."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice de Mortagne was born after 1167, in Béthune, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, her father, Everard III Ralph de Mortagne, was 8870 and her mother, Mathilde de Béthune, was 8865. She had at least 4 sons and 1 daughter with Wouter van Zottegem III."},"et":{"after 1167–":"pärast 1167–Surnud","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1167–Female":"1167–Surnud","1166–1220":"1166–1220","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1191–1227":"1191–1227","1199–1238":"1199–1238","–1173":"–1173","–1220":"–1220","1129–1190":"1129–1190","1135–1191":"1135–1191","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1129":"1129","1238":"1238","1227":"1227","1135":"1135","1167":"1167","1199":"1199","1166":"1166","um 1199":"umbes 1199","after 1167":"pärast 1167","1219":"1219","Ghent, East Flanders, Belgium":"Gent, Oost-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Béthune, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Béthune, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Holland, Noord-Brabant, Netherlands":"Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad"},"fi":{"after 1167–":"1167 jälkeen–Kuollut","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1167–Female":"1167–Kuollut","1166–1220":"1166–1220","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1191–1227":"1191–1227","1199–1238":"1199–1238","–1173":"–1173","–1220":"–1220","1129–1190":"1129–1190","1135–1191":"1135–1191","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1129":"1129","1238":"1238","1227":"1227","1135":"1135","1167":"1167","1199":"1199","1166":"1166","um 1199":"noin 1199","after 1167":"1167 jälkeen","1219":"1219","Ghent, East Flanders, Belgium":"Gent, Oost-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Béthune, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Béthune, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Cala